 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Ursela</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> After buying the game, I started a half-elf warrior in Qeynos because some friends said to start in that area with them.  Reading through the manual on stats, added points to agi, dex, etc since the manual said they help kill things / reduce damage.  Several levels later I meet a little gnome named Victimizer (on Torv).  He has a skeleton with him doing all his fighting.  He didn't even get close to the giant tree (in West Karana) to kill it!  Amazed at how easy that was compared to my Warrior with tarnished weapons, I started a gnecro.</P><P>Well, remembering what the manual said, I put points into agi/dex to make it easier to kill things (Woot 108 starting int for gnomes).  Steamfont/Ak'Anon are great areas, but after four levels (read, several long nights) I wanted to rejoin my friends in Qeynos.  Now I knew all about /loc, I had found eqatlas.com, I was set to make the journey.  I spent who knows how many hours looking at eqatlas, looking at maps zone to zone.  I start the journey.  I die in Butcherblock to the dumb dwarves.  Ok, lesson learned.  I read on CastersRealm about invis at level 8.  I can stick it out...</P><P>I make it to eight on orc hill in GF (many, many more long noob nights .. level 5 and lost corpse there somewhere, /shout Yell if you see my corpse anywhere).  After dinging eight and buying Gather Shadows, I start the journey again.  I make it all the way to Qeynos in about two hours, drop invis, con guards and all is ok.  I figure I should camp and wait for the friends to log on.  No, I just want to explore Qeynos Hills a little more.  As I walk back to the zone, something like a beggar wails on me and roots me.  Dead, and level 7.  Make a little exp to get eight again, get going back to Qeynos, die in Freeport.  Make a little exp, die in Kithicor.  Make a little exp, die in WK.  The next few trips I remember to get bound in Freeport. :)  I think it took three nights before I made it back to Qeynos and was shocked to see my corpse hadn't yet poofed.</P><P>Then it's the usual stuff people have stated.  Fear cost a ton of mana at level 4, didn't try it again until like 15.  After 16 I found this site (the old one), learned about casting darkness and then fear was a good technique for the bard in WK.  After that, life's been much easier.<BR></font></td>
